sequenceDiagram
    participant F as Frontend App
    participant B as Backend Server
    participant O as OIDC Server

    F->>B: Click Login
    B->>B: Generate random state & nonce
    B->>B: Store state & nonce in pending session
    B->>F: 302 Redirect → OIDC /authorize?...&state=xxx&nonce=yyy

    Note over F,B: Browser navigates to OIDC Server directly<br/>No server-to-server call here

    F->>O: GET /authorize?client_id=xxx&redirect_uri=xxx&response_type=code&scope=openid...&state=xxx&nonce=yyy
    O->>O: Validate client_id & redirect_uri against allowlist
    alt redirect_uri invalid
        O->>F: 400 Bad Request (must not redirect — RFC 6749 §4.1.2.1)
    end
    O->>O: Create OIDC Session (AuthorizeRequest)
    O->>O: Store state, nonce & generate csrf_token in session
    O->>O: Save session to cache (TTL: 10 min)
    O->>F: 302 Redirect /sign-in + Set-Cookie auth_session=<session_id> (HttpOnly, SameSite=Lax)

    Note over O,F: SameSite=Lax required — redirect is cross-origin

    F->>O: GET /sign-in
    O->>O: Read OIDC Session via auth_session cookie
    O->>F: Sign-in Page (with hidden csrf_token input)

    F->>O: POST /sign-in (email + password + csrf_token)
    O->>O: Atomically read & delete OIDC Session (GetAndDelete)
    O->>O: Validate csrf_token vs session (constant-time compare)
    alt session not found or csrf_token mismatch
        O->>F: 400 Bad Request (invalid_session)
    end
    O->>O: Look up user by email
    O->>O: Verify password hash
    alt credentials invalid
        O->>O: Increment FailedAttempts, re-save session
        alt FailedAttempts >= 3
            O->>F: 400 Bad Request (max_login_attempts_exceeded)
        end
        O->>F: 401 Unauthorized (invalid_email_or_password)
    end
    O->>O: Generate Auth Code (TTL: 5 min)
    O->>O: Save Auth Code with nonce & scope in cache
    O->>F: 303 Redirect (See Other) redirect_uri?code=zzz&state=xxx + Clear auth_session cookie (MaxAge=-1)

    F->>B: GET /callback?code=zzz&state=xxx
    B->>B: Validate state matches pending session
    alt state missing or mismatch
        B->>F: 400 Bad Request (state mismatch)
    end

    Note over B,O: POST /token is server-to-server<br/>Backend calls OIDC Server directly

    B->>O: POST /token (grant_type=authorization_code + code + client_id + redirect_uri)
    O->>O: Consume Auth Code (one-time use, GetAndDelete)
    alt code not found, already consumed, or expired
        O->>B: 400 Bad Request (auth code not found)
    end
    O->>O: Validate client_id and redirect_uri match Auth Code
    alt client_id or redirect_uri mismatch
        O->>B: 400 Bad Request (invalid_grant)
    end
    Note over O,B: This test harness sends no code_challenge,<br/>so this branch is dormant here — shown for completeness<br/>since the server validates PKCE when a client provides it
    alt code_challenge present on Auth Code
        O->>O: Hash code_verifier (S256) & compare with stored code_challenge
        alt code_verifier missing or mismatch
            O->>B: 400 Bad Request (invalid_grant)
        end
    end
    O->>O: Generate Access Token + ID Token (with nonce claim) + Refresh Token
    O->>O: Save Refresh Token server-side (for future revocation)
    O->>B: Access Token + ID Token + Refresh Token (JSON)

    B->>B: Decode ID Token payload
    B->>B: Validate nonce claim matches pending session
    alt nonce mismatch
        B->>F: 400 Bad Request (nonce mismatch)
    end
    B->>B: Clear pending session
    B->>B: Store tokens in session
    B->>F: 302 Redirect to home

    Note over F,O: --- Token Refresh (same /token endpoint, grant_type=refresh_token) ---

    F->>B: API call with expired access token
    B->>O: POST /token (grant_type=refresh_token + refresh_token + client_id)
    O->>O: Hash refresh_token (SHA256), look up by hash
    alt not found, revoked, or expired
        O->>B: 401 Unauthorized (invalid_refresh_token)
    end
    O->>O: Look up user, reject if AuthenticatedAt predates SessionsInvalidatedAt
    alt session invalidated
        O->>B: 401 Unauthorized (invalid_refresh_token)
    end
    O->>O: Generate new Access Token + ID Token + Refresh Token
    O->>O: Revoke old Refresh Token (rotation) & save new one — preserves AuthenticatedAt & DeviceID
    O->>B: New Access Token + ID Token + Refresh Token (JSON)
    B->>B: Store new tokens in session

    Note over O: Refresh Token TTL: 30 days

    Note over F,O: --- Token Revocation (POST /oidc/revoke, RFC 7009) ---

    F->>B: Click "revoke session" / sign out of one device
    B->>O: POST /oidc/revoke (Bearer access token) — token + token_type_hint?
    O->>O: Try as Refresh Token - hash & look up, verify caller owns it (UserID == CallerID)
    alt found & owned
        O->>O: Mark RevokedAt (one-time revoke)
    else not a refresh token, or not owned
        O->>O: Parse as Access Token JWT, extract jti & subject
        alt jti present & subject == CallerID
            O->>O: Blacklist jti in cache (TTL = token's remaining expiry)
        end
    end
    O->>B: 200 OK, empty body (silent no-op on unknown/foreign/wrong-owner tokens per RFC 7009 §2.2 — storage/cache errors still surface as failures)

    Note over F,O: --- Logout (GET /oidc/logout) ---

    F->>O: GET /oidc/logout?id_token_hint=...&post_logout_redirect_uri=...
    O->>O: Resolve UserID (priority: access token subject → id_token_hint subject → refresh_token cookie)
    O->>O: Blacklist Access Token jti in cache (if present & not expired)
    O->>O: Revoke ALL Refresh Tokens for UserID (RevokeAllForUser)
    alt post_logout_redirect_uri provided & in allowlist
        O->>F: 302 Redirect to post_logout_redirect_uri + Clear refresh_token cookie (MaxAge=-1)
    else
        O->>F: 200 OK + Clear refresh_token cookie (MaxAge=-1)
    end

    Note over O: Always succeeds — best-effort cleanup, never fails on missing/invalid credentials
